cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use OncoBiome Swarm in your research, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "OncoBiome Swarm: A Large Language Model-Based Multi-Agent Framework for Emergent Simulation of the KRAS G12D Pancreatic Tumor Microenvironment"
version: "0.4.0"
date-released: "2026-03-24"
url: "https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/oncobiome-swarm"
repository-code: "https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/oncobiome-swarm"
license: "LicenseRef-OncoBiome-Dual"
abstract: >
  OncoBiome Swarm is a novel LLM-driven agent-based modeling (ABM) framework
  in which every biological agent in the tumor microenvironment (TME) reasons
  independently via a large language model with persistent memory. Applied to
  KRAS G12D pancreatic ductal adenocarcinoma (PDAC), the framework reproduces
  nine emergent immunosuppressive mechanisms — including cold TME formation,
  immunoediting equilibrium, NK exhaustion preceding CD8+ collapse, and
  tolerogenic DC phenotype — that deterministic rule-based systems cannot model.
  Sprint 4 introduces Natural Killer (NK) and Dendritic Cell (DC) agents,
  quantitative RMSE validation, sensitivity analysis, and n=3 reproducibility
  for the innate-adaptive bridge experiment.
keywords:
  - tumor microenvironment
  - agent-based modeling
  - large language models
  - KRAS G12D
  - pancreatic cancer
  - NK cells
  - dendritic cells
  - immunosuppression
  - emergent behavior
  - multi-agent systems
  - computational oncology
